    Class Description
    Assertions
    General test assertions that may be helpful in unit tests.
    ConcurrentHelpers
    Helper methods and test assertions related to concurrent data structures.
    Handler
    An object or lambda that handles HTTP requests for a HttpServer.
    Handlers
    Factory methods for standard Handler implementations.
    Handlers.SSE
    Shortcut handlers for simulating a Server-Sent Events stream.
    HandlerSwitcher
    A delegator that forwards requests to another handler, which can be changed at any time.
    HttpServer
    A simplified wrapper for an embedded test HTTP server.
    HttpServer.Delegate
    An abstraction for the part of the server implementation that could vary by platform.
    HttpServer.Delegate.Factory
    Factory pattern for the server abstraction.
    HttpServerImpl
    This class just contains the reference to the specific HTTP server implementation we will use, so that HttpServer can contain only portable code.
    JsonAssertions
    Test assertions and matchers related to JSON.
    JsonTestValue
    A simple wrapper for a string that can be parsed as JSON for tests.
    RequestContext
    An abstraction used by Handler implementations to hide the details of the underlying HTTP server framework.
    RequestInfo
    Properties of a request received by HttpServer.
    RequestRecorder
    An object that records all requests.
    ServerTLSConfiguration
    Holds all certificate/key data required to configure an HttpServer for HTTPS, and to configure a client to make requests to that server.
    SimpleRouter
    A delegator that provides simple request path/method matching.
    SpecialHttpConfigurations
    Testing tools for validating that HTTP client logic is correctly applying configuration parameters.
    SpecialHttpConfigurations.Params
    See SpecialHttpConfigurations.TestAction.
    SpecialHttpConfigurations.TestAction
    Implemented by the caller to perform some action against an HTTP server.
    SpecialHttpConfigurations.UnexpectedResponseException
    See SpecialHttpConfigurations.TestAction.
    TcpHandler
    Use with TcpServer to define behavior for a TCP endpoint in a test.
    TcpHandlers
    Factory methods for standard TcpHandler implementations.
    TcpServer
    A simple mechanism for creating a TCP listener and configuring its behavior.
    TempDir
    Provides a temporary directory for use by a test.
    TempFile
    Provides a temporary file for use by a test.
    TypeBehavior
    Test assertions that may be helpful in testing generic type behavior.
    TypeBehavior.ValueFactory<T>
    A supplier interface for use TypeBehavior.checkEqualsAndHashCode(List).
